{"article_id":"iQaW8TGXKJGJISLG","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Mississippi appears headed for a runoff in its donnybrook of a GOP Senate primary .","depth":4},{"id":1,"text":"That ' s bad news for the Republican establishment ,","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"good news for the tea party","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"- and cause for Democratic hope in November ,","depth":7},{"id":4,"text":"despite the state ' s deep-red hue .","depth":7},{"id":5,"text":"Tea party-backed state Sen. Chris McDaniel leads six-term Sen. Thad Cochran by just over 2,000 votes ,","depth":6},{"id":6,"text":"with 99.5 percent of precincts reporting as of Wednesday morning .","depth":6},{"id":7,"text":"More important ,","depth":7},{"id":8,"text":"with a third candidate taking a sliver of the vote ,","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"neither of the top two candidates won a majority .","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"If that result holds ,","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"Mr. McDaniel and Senator Cochran will go head-to-head in a runoff June 24 .","depth":7},{"id":12,"text":"\" In a runoff it is hard to see how McDaniel is not a slight favorite ,","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"as his supporters are driven by something","depth":10},{"id":14,"text":"Cochran ' s aren ' t -","depth":10},{"id":15,"text":"excitement , \"","depth":9},{"id":16,"text":"says Republican strategist Ford O ' Connell .","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"\" Runoffs usually entail a much lower turnout .","depth":8},{"id":18,"text":"Therefore the candidate","depth":10},{"id":19,"text":"whose core supporters have more intensity","depth":10},{"id":20,"text":"tend to win . \"","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"And the tea party is all about intensity .","depth":7},{"id":22,"text":"In addition , Cochran has appeared tired ,","depth":7},{"id":23,"text":"especially compared with the youthful McDaniel .","depth":7},{"id":24,"text":"Cochran declined to debate McDaniel .","depth":6},{"id":25,"text":"If McDaniel wins the runoff ,","depth":7},{"id":26,"text":"Democrats will have a rare","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"- if slight -","depth":10},{"id":28,"text":"chance","depth":9},{"id":29,"text":"of winning a Republican-held seat in a cycle","depth":9},{"id":30,"text":"that generally favors the GOP .","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"Democrats recruited former Rep. Travis Childers , a Blue Dog Democrat","depth":8},{"id":32,"text":"who held a solidly Republican House seat from 2008 to 2010 ,","depth":8},{"id":33,"text":"precisely in the hopes","depth":8},{"id":34,"text":"that McDaniel would beat Cochran .","depth":8},{"id":35,"text":"Democrats are desperately trying to keep control of the Senate","depth":8},{"id":36,"text":"and have far more vulnerable seats","depth":9},{"id":37,"text":"than do the Republicans .","depth":9},{"id":38,"text":"McDaniel is new to big-time politics ,","depth":8},{"id":39,"text":"and Democrats have visions of another Todd Akin , the Republican nominee in the 2012 Senate race in Missouri","depth":9},{"id":40,"text":"who squandered victory with comments on \" legitimate rape. \"","depth":9},{"id":41,"text":"Last month , the Mississippi primary descended into nastiness","depth":9},{"id":42,"text":"when four tea party McDaniel supporters were arrested over a breakin into the nursing home of Cochran ' s bedridden wife .","depth":10},{"id":43,"text":"A video","depth":13},{"id":44,"text":"containing pictures of Mrs. Cochran","depth":13},{"id":45,"text":"was posted on the web ,","depth":12},{"id":46,"text":"but later taken down .","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"The scandal threw McDaniel off-message","depth":9},{"id":48,"text":"and halted his momentum , but not permanently .","depth":9},{"id":49,"text":"Chism Strategies , a Democratic firm","depth":10},{"id":50,"text":"that polled the race ,","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"found","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"that McDaniel had regained his footing by last Friday .","depth":8},{"id":53,"text":"Still , McDaniel is a riskier bet than Cochran in November .","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"Cochran has been a fixture in Washington","depth":8},{"id":55,"text":"representing Mississippi for 42 years , first in the House , then the Senate .","depth":8},{"id":56,"text":"McDaniel has served in the state Senate for six years ,","depth":8},{"id":57,"text":"but is new to statewide politics .","depth":8},{"id":58,"text":"And","depth":6},{"id":59,"text":"if he wins the nomination ,","depth":7},{"id":60,"text":"the Democrats will throw everything","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"they can into the race","depth":9},{"id":62,"text":"- both money and extensive opposition research .","depth":8},{"id":63,"text":"A trial lawyer by profession ,","depth":8},{"id":64,"text":"McDaniel is also a former talk radio host ,","depth":9},{"id":65,"text":"giving Democrats plenty","depth":10},{"id":66,"text":"to dig into .","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"During the primary , an old recording of his show surfaced with provocative statements on women , Mexicans , and slaves .","depth":9},{"id":68,"text":"The comments garnered some attention ,","depth":10},{"id":69,"text":"but nothing like the nursing home scandal .","depth":10},{"id":70,"text":"Earlier in the campaign , McDaniel also stumbled","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"when asked by a reporter about aid to Mississippi after hurricane Katrina .","depth":9},{"id":72,"text":"As a tea party Republican , McDaniel is preaching less reliance on Washington","depth":7},{"id":73,"text":"- a position","depth":8},{"id":74,"text":"that seems anathema to a state","depth":9},{"id":75,"text":"heavily dependent on federal aid .","depth":9},{"id":76,"text":"But it may be a new day in Mississippi .","depth":6},{"id":77,"text":"The last time","depth":11},{"id":78,"text":"the state denied renomination to a senator","depth":11},{"id":79,"text":"was in 1942 ,","depth":10},{"id":80,"text":"according to John Gizzi , political editor of Newsmax .","depth":9},{"id":81,"text":"Electing a Democrat is another story .","depth":8},{"id":82,"text":"The last Democrat","depth":10},{"id":83,"text":"to represent Mississippi in the Senate","depth":10},{"id":84,"text":"was John Stennis , an old-time Southern Democrat","depth":10},{"id":85,"text":"who retired in 1988 .","depth":10},{"id":86,"text":"During his one term in Congress , Mr. Childers voted against Obamacare and gun restrictions ,","depth":9},{"id":87,"text":"and he opposes same-sex marriage .","depth":9},{"id":88,"text":"Childers is seen as the strongest recruit","depth":7},{"id":89,"text":"the Democrats could have hoped for ,","depth":7},{"id":90,"text":"but he ' s still a long shot .","depth":6},{"id":91,"text":"If Cochran manages to win the primary ,","depth":7},{"id":92,"text":"there are suggestions","depth":8},{"id":93,"text":"Childers will drop out .","depth":8},{"id":94,"text":"But against McDaniel , he will have to hope for a major gaffe or scandal .","depth":6},{"id":95,"text":"Get the Monitor Stories","depth":5},{"id":96,"text":"you care about","depth":5},{"id":97,"text":"delivered to your inbox .","depth":4},{"id":98,"text":"By signing up ,","depth":4},{"id":99,"text":"you agree to our Privacy Policy","depth":4},{"id":100,"text":"Mississippi Republicans pooh-pooh Childers ' s chances altogether .","depth":8},{"id":101,"text":"They note","depth":9},{"id":102,"text":"that in 2008 ,","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"when former Democratic Gov . Ronnie Musgrove challenged appointed Sen. Roger Wicker","depth":12},{"id":104,"text":"( R ) ,","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"Mr. Musgrove lost by 10 percentage points .","depth":11},{"id":106,"text":"If ever a Democrat could have won ,","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"that was the time .","depth":9},{"id":108,"text":"It was a Democratic wave year ,","depth":9},{"id":109,"text":"and","depth":10},{"id":110,"text":"with Barack Obama on the ballot in his first presidential election , black turnout was high .","depth":10},{"id":111,"text":"Mississippi ' s population is 37 percent African American .","depth":6},{"id":112,"text":"But for now , Mississippi has a real barn-burner on its hands .","depth":5},{"id":113,"text":"As of 8 a.m. Eastern time Wednesday , McDaniel led with 49.6 percent of the vote ,","depth":6},{"id":114,"text":"and Cochran had 48.9 percent ,","depth":7},{"id":115,"text":"with 99.5 percent of the precincts reporting .","depth":7},{"id":116,"text":"The difference is 2,128 votes .","depth":5},{"id":117,"text":"If the final count gives neither man a majority ,","depth":4},{"id":118,"text":"there ' s a three-week sprint to the runoff on June 24 .","depth":4}],"relations":[{"parent":237,"left":213,"right":236,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":213,"left":143,"right":212,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":143,"left":123,"right":142,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":123,"left":0,"right":122,"relation":"evaluation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":122,"left":1,"right":121,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":121,"left":2,"right":120,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":120,"left":3,"right":4,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":142,"left":129,"right":141,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":129,"left":124,"right":128,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":124,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":128,"left":126,"right":127,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":126,"left":7,"right":125,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":125,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":127,"left":10,"right":11,"relation":"condition","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":141,"left":138,"right":140,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":138,"left":133,"right":137,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":133,"left":132,"right":16,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":132,"left":12,"right":131,"relation":"explanation","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":131,"left":130,"ri